John Victor Roos Sells 228 Shares of Salesforce.com Inc (CRM) Stock

					Posted by Anthony Sawyer on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 


Tweet












Salesforce.com Inc (NYSE:CRM) Director John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, July 13th. The shares were sold at an average price of $90.50, for a total transaction of $20,634.00. Following the completion of the sale, the director now owns 16,360 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $1,480,580. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is accessible through this link. 
John Victor Roos also recently made the following trade(s): 


 Get Salesforce.com Inc alerts:




On Thursday, July 20th, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $89.69, for a total transaction of $20,449.32. 
On Thursday, July 6th, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $86.62, for a total transaction of $19,749.36. 
On Thursday, June 29th, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $87.65, for a total transaction of $19,984.20. 
On Thursday, June 22nd, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $88.03, for a total transaction of $20,070.84. 
On Thursday, June 15th, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $85.99, for a total transaction of $19,605.72. 
On Thursday, June 8th, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $91.39, for a total transaction of $20,836.92. 
On Thursday, June 1st, John Victor Roos sold 228 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $90.00, for a total transaction of $20,520.00. 
On Thursday, May 25th, John Victor Roos sold 191 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $90.04, for a total transaction of $17,197.64. 
On Thursday, May 18th, John Victor Roos sold 194 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $87.90, for a total transaction of $17,052.60. 
On Thursday, May 11th, John Victor Roos sold 194 shares of Salesforce.com stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $87.16, for a total transaction of $16,909.04. 

Shares of Salesforce.com Inc (NYSE CRM) traded down 0.94% on Friday, reaching $89.69. 2,928,673 shares of the company were exchanged. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $88.47 and its 200 day moving average price is $84.01. Salesforce.com Inc has a 12 month low of $66.43 and a 12 month high of $91.99. The company has a market cap of $63.88 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 474.55 and a beta of 1.28. 




Salesforce.com (NYSE:CRM) last released its earnings results on Thursday, May 18th. The CRM provider reported $0.28 earnings per share for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.26 by $0.02. The business had revenue of $2.39 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.35 billion. Salesforce.com had a net margin of 1.49% and a return on equity of 1.80%. The company’s revenue for the quarter was up 24.6% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the prior year, the firm posted $0.24 EPS.  On average, equities research analysts expect that  Salesforce.com Inc will post $1.30 EPS for the current year. 
