                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    4:35 PM ET 06/21/2017
                                                


Oracle Corp's (ORCL) quarterly profit blew past analysts' estimates as the business software maker's big push towards cloud-based products and services paid off. The company's shares were up 5 percent at $48.74 in after-market trading on Wednesday. Oracle said cloud-computing and on-premise software business revenue rose 5.3 percent to $8.88 billion in the fourth quarter ended May 31.

















